08:48.749 --> 08:52.851
<i>♪ The undertow of gloom ♪</i>

08:52.853 --> 08:59.161
<i>♪ In the gloom ♪</i>

09:00.627 --> 09:08.036
<i>♪ Drowning in
The deep blue sea ♪</i>

09:24.819 --> 09:27.419
[MAN COUGHS, THEN SNIFFS]

09:27.421 --> 09:29.489
I can't believe
he didn't eat you.

09:29.491 --> 09:32.290
[CHUCKLES] Well, luckily I
wouldn't taste very good to him.

09:32.292 --> 09:35.160
You know the idea
that great whites are these

09:35.162 --> 09:37.496
malicious killing machines
roving the shorelines

09:37.498 --> 09:39.298
looking for some swimmer
to chomp on

09:39.300 --> 09:41.900
is just pure fiction
perpetuated by Hollywood.

09:41.902 --> 09:47.941
I mean, these magnificent and
unfairly represented creatures

09:47.943 --> 09:50.043
are simply looking for fish.

09:50.045 --> 09:52.044
Or a nice, fat seal to eat.

09:52.046 --> 09:54.413
You know, any time
there is a human attack,

09:54.415 --> 09:56.948
it's just a case
of mistaken identity.

09:56.950 --> 10:00.285
Sharks are an extremely
important part

10:00.287 --> 10:01.888
of our ocean's ecosystem.

10:01.890 --> 10:05.390
And, sadly,
they are being killed

10:05.392 --> 10:10.163
at an average rate
of 100 million per year.

10:10.165 --> 10:13.502
For a purpose as frivolous
as a bowl of fin soup.

10:15.603 --> 10:19.672
That is why the institute
my mother founded,

10:19.674 --> 10:24.409
Five Oceans Institute, is fully
dedicated to shark research

10:24.411 --> 10:27.212
and to educating the public
on how important it is

10:27.214 --> 10:29.283
to protect the species.

10:30.551 --> 10:32.018
Yeah.

10:32.020 --> 10:35.453
Your video shows you swimming
with a wide variety of sharks.

10:35.455 --> 10:38.259
Is there any type of shark
you wouldn't swim with?

10:40.395 --> 10:41.626
Bull sharks.

10:41.628 --> 10:45.231
They're the most lethal
of all the shark species.

10:45.233 --> 10:48.233
They tend to blast their prey
with the thick part

10:48.235 --> 10:49.669
of their skull
to disable them,

10:49.671 --> 10:52.770
and then, uh, clamp down
like a pit bull.

10:52.772 --> 10:56.275
And their bite is 10 times
that of a great white, so,

10:56.277 --> 10:58.711
yeah, they're quite
intimidating to swim with.

10:58.713 --> 11:01.283
[♪♪♪]

11:10.123 --> 11:11.557
Aaron, you on comms?

11:11.559 --> 11:14.393
AARON [ON RADIO]:
Roger, Trent. I got eyes on you.

11:14.395 --> 11:17.265
Open fence section 5F.

11:39.421 --> 11:42.221
You come back with an expression
like that on your face,

11:42.223 --> 11:43.923
I know there's
a story behind it.

11:43.925 --> 11:45.794
Yeah, not one
I wanna spread.

11:47.061 --> 11:48.528
We had a jail break
today.

11:48.530 --> 11:50.129
How many?

11:50.131 --> 11:51.362
All five.

11:51.364 --> 11:52.999
That's five too many, man.

11:53.001 --> 11:55.366
Yeah, no shit.

11:55.368 --> 11:58.136
I gotta check
the perimeter fence.

11:58.138 --> 12:00.541
Those fish
can't get out again.

12:09.617 --> 12:12.784
MISTY: Lastly, I'd like to
thank you for having me.

12:12.786 --> 12:14.086
[AUDIENCE CLAPPING]

12:14.088 --> 12:15.623
Thank you.

12:26.935 --> 12:28.433
Dr. Calhoun.

12:28.435 --> 12:29.400
Yes?

12:29.402 --> 12:31.437
Misty, my name
is Craig Burns.

12:31.439 --> 12:33.474
Hi, what can I do for you?

12:36.344 --> 12:40.178
Durant Pharmaceuticals.
I'm not a pharma doc.

12:40.180 --> 12:41.581
What am I missing?

12:41.583 --> 12:43.649
My client, Mr. Durant,
is a fan of your work.

12:43.651 --> 12:45.518
He considers you
the most astute expert

12:45.520 --> 12:47.519
in shark behavior
in the world.

12:47.521 --> 12:50.121
He'd like you to consult on
a new project of his.

12:50.123 --> 12:51.558
A conservation project?

12:51.560 --> 12:54.161
He prefers to call it
the preservation of man.

12:55.464 --> 12:57.362
So you continued
your mother's work?

12:57.364 --> 12:59.631
She was the one that taught
you to love the ocean?

12:59.633 --> 13:02.168
- She taught me to respect it.
- [SCOFFS]

13:02.170 --> 13:04.636
You're not filling in all
the blanks, Mr. Burns.

13:04.638 --> 13:07.707
Why is a pharma company
interested in working with me?

13:07.709 --> 13:10.909
Mr. Durant would love the chance
to answer your questions.

13:10.911 --> 13:12.712
When?

13:12.714 --> 13:14.349
Tomorrow.

13:16.383 --> 13:18.583
Fifty thousand dollars?

13:18.585 --> 13:21.319
- For what?
- To share your expertise.

13:21.321 --> 13:23.555
That's yours, Dr. Calhoun,
whether you decide

13:23.557 --> 13:25.890
to work with us or not.
Call it a down payment.

13:25.892 --> 13:28.059
But should you choose
to come on board,

13:28.061 --> 13:29.595
Mr. Durant is
prepared to fully fund

13:29.597 --> 13:32.264
your work at the Five Oceans
for the next five years.

13:32.266 --> 13:33.731
And from what
I've read recently,

13:33.733 --> 13:35.534
your institute
could use the money.

13:35.536 --> 13:38.672
Something about
a grant withdrawal, if I recall?

13:42.076 --> 13:45.613
Aren't you even a little curious
about what we're doing?

13:51.886 --> 13:53.822
[♪♪♪]

14:16.176 --> 14:17.778
TRENT:
Aaron.

14:20.614 --> 14:22.515
What's the most
important rule here?

14:22.517 --> 14:27.622
Don't piss into the wind and
don't pull on Superman's cape.

14:30.324 --> 14:32.391
Yeah. No, no,
that's-that's the second

14:32.393 --> 14:34.026
most important rule,
of course.

14:34.028 --> 14:38.499
The first most important rule is
always keep the fences green.

14:39.901 --> 14:41.100
[COMPUTER CHIRPS]

14:41.102 --> 14:42.635
Which they are, dude.

14:42.637 --> 14:45.170
They were green this morning,
they'll be green tonight.

14:45.172 --> 14:46.505
I don't sleep on my job.

14:46.507 --> 14:48.506
Then how do you explain

14:48.508 --> 14:51.845
five sharks going
for a goddamn joy swim?

14:53.915 --> 14:56.818
Hey, man, look, that's...
That's not possible.

14:57.852 --> 14:59.751
I swear, look.

14:59.753 --> 15:01.520
- [COMPUTER CHIRPS]
- You see?

15:01.522 --> 15:03.956
System's working perfectly,
just like I programmed.

15:03.958 --> 15:06.358
Yeah, and I'm telling you,
those sharks were out

15:06.360 --> 15:07.927
in the open ocean.

15:07.929 --> 15:10.062
I don't get... Jesus!

15:10.064 --> 15:11.797
You see?

15:11.799 --> 15:15.768
They avoid that electrical field
like the plague.

15:15.770 --> 15:18.837
[♪♪♪]

15:18.839 --> 15:20.809
Wait a minute.

15:23.276 --> 15:25.412
What the hell?

15:27.080 --> 15:29.280
What is that?

15:29.282 --> 15:30.685
A tunnel?

15:31.819 --> 15:34.086
That's a tunnel
under the cable!

15:34.088 --> 15:36.024
Sharks can't do that.

15:38.191 --> 15:39.594
Can they?

15:41.228 --> 15:43.162
We gotta extend
the fence's range.

15:43.164 --> 15:47.098
It'll take us a week to get
more cable down from Cape Town.

15:47.100 --> 15:49.568
We don't have
that much time.

15:49.570 --> 15:51.337
Should I notify the boss?

15:51.339 --> 15:53.808
No. No, not yet.

15:55.142 --> 15:57.012
I got an idea.

16:07.955 --> 16:10.959
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

16:21.002 --> 16:22.971
[SIGHS]

16:25.305 --> 16:27.840
You have gotta
be kidding me.

16:27.842 --> 16:29.274
Misty.

16:29.276 --> 16:31.410
This is Daniel
and Leslie Kim.

16:31.412 --> 16:35.481
Daniel is a neurophysiologist.
Leslie is a neurobiologist.

16:35.483 --> 16:37.949
Leslie, Daniel,
meet Dr. Misty Calhoun.

16:37.951 --> 16:39.985
Misty is a marine
conservationist

16:39.987 --> 16:42.520
who has singlehandedly removed
three shark species

16:42.522 --> 16:44.656
- from the endangered list.
- Wow.

16:44.658 --> 16:47.360
So a neurophysiologist,
a neurobiologist,

16:47.362 --> 16:51.429
and a shark conservationist
enter a bar.

16:51.431 --> 16:52.930
What's the punchline?

16:52.932 --> 16:55.500
No punchline, just
an international murderer's row

16:55.502 --> 16:57.101
of brilliant minds.

16:57.103 --> 16:59.571
If you'll excuse me,
I need to talk to the captain.

16:59.573 --> 17:02.510
We should arrive at
the complex by 1500 hours.

17:03.377 --> 17:04.609
[SIGHS]

17:04.612 --> 17:06.044
Did you guys sign this NDA?

17:06.046 --> 17:08.479
I got a headache
just trying to get through it.

17:08.481 --> 17:10.148
Oh, good, so it's not just me.

17:10.151 --> 17:12.483
It's some lawyer
trying to justify his job.

17:12.486 --> 17:14.387
But you did sign it?

17:14.388 --> 17:17.422
[LAUGHING] Oh, yeah, we've been
waiting for this opportunity.

17:17.424 --> 17:20.321
You act like
we already know it's great.

17:20.324 --> 17:20.825
It's a big if, Daniel.

17:20.827 --> 17:22.328
[SIGHING]
But it's Carl Durant.

17:22.329 --> 17:25.330
I mean, the guy's made of money,
and he gets things done.

17:25.333 --> 17:28.300
And after this weekend,
funding won't be something

17:28.301 --> 17:30.069
we need to
worry about anymore.

17:30.071 --> 17:32.170
Yeah, he is throwing
his money around.

17:32.172 --> 17:35.440
We're newlyweds,
so don't mind the PDA.

17:35.442 --> 17:37.342
Sorry.

17:37.344 --> 17:39.143
It is crazy to pack
an overnight bag,

17:39.145 --> 17:41.612
and head out to sea not knowing
what we're in for.

17:41.614 --> 17:43.448
Yeah, I did
a little research myself,

17:43.450 --> 17:44.883
but nothing's really
adding up.

17:44.885 --> 17:47.453
I'm baffled as to why I'm here.

17:47.455 --> 17:50.658
Well, I guess we'll all
find out together, then.

19:08.268 --> 19:11.169
This is it?
Here you go.

19:11.171 --> 19:12.806
- Thank you.
- Of course.

19:14.842 --> 19:17.845
- Watch your step.
- Thank you.

19:21.582 --> 19:24.182
[GRUNTS]

19:24.184 --> 19:25.686
Mike.

19:26.553 --> 19:28.320
Welcome to Akheilos.

19:28.322 --> 19:30.422
You mean Akheilos?

19:30.424 --> 19:32.826
As in the child Zeus
turned into a shark?

19:33.628 --> 19:34.826
That's the one.

19:34.828 --> 19:36.930
Please, follow me.

19:46.407 --> 19:48.543
[♪♪♪]

20:04.391 --> 20:06.524
TRENT:
Okay, power it up.

20:06.526 --> 20:08.662
[ELECTRICITY BUZZING]

20:21.374 --> 20:23.310
[PANTING]

20:31.885 --> 20:33.819
Mike, recharge the battery.

20:33.821 --> 20:35.924
I need to lay down
another set of rings.

20:40.760 --> 20:43.461
I think you need
a new DPV.

20:43.463 --> 20:45.330
Gets the job done.

20:45.332 --> 20:48.266
I see you've met our head
of operations, Trent Slater.

20:48.268 --> 20:49.935
Trent,

20:49.937 --> 20:52.206
this is
Dr. Misty Calhoun.

20:53.373 --> 20:56.140
You mind if I ask
what those are for?

20:56.142 --> 20:58.509
We're reinforcing
the fence perimeter.

20:58.511 --> 21:01.080
This entire complex
is surrounded by those rings?

21:01.082 --> 21:03.649
No, we're surrounded
by electrical cable

21:03.651 --> 21:05.050
that runs along
the sea floor.

21:05.052 --> 21:06.817
These rings are
coated in graphite,

21:06.819 --> 21:08.719
an excellent conductor
of electricity,

21:08.721 --> 21:10.021
as I'm sure you're aware.

21:10.023 --> 21:11.689
We're using these
rings to extend

21:11.691 --> 21:13.792
the range of
the electric field.

21:13.794 --> 21:17.428
Just an extra bit
of insurance.

21:17.430 --> 21:20.200
What exactly are you guys
trying to keep out?

21:21.602 --> 21:23.271
It's what we're
trying to keep in.

21:24.571 --> 21:26.708
[♪♪♪]

21:28.275 --> 21:30.842
Those are bull sharks.

21:30.844 --> 21:33.445
What are you doing with
bull sharks in containment?

21:33.447 --> 21:35.080
Welcome,
welcome.

21:35.082 --> 21:37.182
I see you've met
our test subjects.

21:37.184 --> 21:39.083
How many do you have?

21:39.085 --> 21:43.455
Five, including Bella.
I'm Carl Durant, you must be...?

21:43.457 --> 21:45.024
Uninterested
in small talk.

21:45.026 --> 21:47.759
You mind explaining to me
what it is you're doing with...

21:47.761 --> 21:49.061
[SIGHS]

21:49.063 --> 21:50.728
...what is it,
you referred to them as?

21:50.730 --> 21:51.863
Your test subjects?

21:51.865 --> 21:53.532
Very important
test subjects.

21:53.534 --> 21:55.367
You know,
sharks aren't lab mice.

21:55.369 --> 21:57.201
[LAUGHS]

21:57.203 --> 21:58.803
I love your passion.

21:58.805 --> 22:02.239
Yeah, but do you mind, I'd like
to finish the introductions.

22:02.241 --> 22:04.243
Yeah, I'm Misty.

22:04.245 --> 22:05.878
Well, hello.

22:05.880 --> 22:09.714
That's Dr. Daniel Kim
and Dr. Leslie Kim.

22:09.716 --> 22:11.984
Daniel, Leslie,
Carl Durant.

22:11.986 --> 22:13.784
Now everyone
knows everyone.

22:13.786 --> 22:16.787
What you may not
know is that

22:16.789 --> 22:18.957
those are a disaster
waiting to happen

22:18.959 --> 22:21.025
DURANT: I'm sorry,
when I asked you here,

22:21.027 --> 22:23.328
you must have assumed
I was working with sharks.

22:23.330 --> 22:27.166
Well, I never make assumptions,
but working with bull sharks is

22:27.168 --> 22:28.233
a bad idea.

22:28.235 --> 22:30.435
Yes. They are

22:30.437 --> 22:33.671
a bit more dangerous
than traditional lab rats,

22:33.673 --> 22:35.840
but no one is gonna
get hurt out here.

22:35.842 --> 22:38.143
You can't guarantee that.

22:38.145 --> 22:40.845
Actually, I can.

22:40.847 --> 22:43.916
Would you all please
follow me topside?

22:43.918 --> 22:46.821
I have something
I'd like to show you.

22:50.190 --> 22:52.224
You really
busted his chops.

22:52.226 --> 22:53.758
I was just
telling the truth.

22:53.760 --> 22:55.393
Yeah, well,
don't stop.

22:55.395 --> 22:58.031
We could use some
more of it around here.

23:13.146 --> 23:14.946
Well, the floor is yours,
young man.

23:14.948 --> 23:16.348
Well, as Mr. Durant said,

23:16.350 --> 23:19.584
we have an extensive
safety protocol, which...

23:19.586 --> 23:21.288
[YELLS]

23:22.322 --> 23:23.688
Seriously?

23:23.690 --> 23:25.690
[AARON YELLING]

23:25.692 --> 23:28.493
- DANIEL: Swim, dude!
- LESLIE: Somebody do something!

23:28.495 --> 23:30.661
[♪♪♪]

23:30.663 --> 23:32.266
DANIEL:
Hang on, dude!

23:33.767 --> 23:35.335
Whoa!

23:36.437 --> 23:37.601
Oh, my God.

23:37.603 --> 23:38.938
Oh, my God,
I don't see him.

23:38.940 --> 23:41.241
- I don't see him!
- Where'd he go?

23:43.276 --> 23:45.709
DANIEL: Are you guys not
going to do anything?

23:45.711 --> 23:47.044
Do you guys see this?

23:47.046 --> 23:49.851
Hey, stay calm! Stay calm!

23:56.055 --> 23:57.989
LESLIE:
Oh, my God.

23:57.991 --> 24:00.258
Oh, my gosh.

24:00.260 --> 24:01.926
DANIEL:
Help's on the way!

24:01.928 --> 24:03.094
LESLIE:
Be quick!

24:03.096 --> 24:04.830
- Oh, my God.
- MISTY: Are you okay?

24:04.832 --> 24:08.333
This is not what
I call okay! Oh, God!

24:08.335 --> 24:11.101
LESLIE: You can make it!
Oh, my gosh!

24:11.103 --> 24:12.938
- DANIEL: Swim faster!
- Oh, my God.

24:12.940 --> 24:14.105
Five more seconds.

24:14.107 --> 24:15.876
- Don't look back!
- Come on!

24:17.378 --> 24:19.143
Come on, you guys.

24:19.145 --> 24:20.778
- [REMOTE CHIRPS]
- DANIEL: Come on.

24:20.780 --> 24:23.515
- LESLIE: Oh, my God.
- DANIEL: Oh, my gosh.

24:23.517 --> 24:25.583
DANIEL: Come on,
you're almost there.

24:25.585 --> 24:27.218
[PANTING]

24:27.220 --> 24:29.990
- DANIEL: Come on, guys.
- LESLIE: You can make it!

24:31.024 --> 24:33.161
- [MISTY PANTING]
- [AARON GRUNTING]

24:35.228 --> 24:38.565
LESLIE:
Oh, my God, oh, my God.

24:40.601 --> 24:41.800
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

24:41.802 --> 24:43.168
Better get
a raise for that.

24:43.170 --> 24:46.036
Sorry, Aaron.
I have a flair for the dramatic,

24:46.038 --> 24:47.339
but you were
perfectly safe.

24:47.341 --> 24:48.907
Did you think that
was funny?

24:48.909 --> 24:51.409
I think it was
an effective demonstration.

24:51.411 --> 24:54.545
You're condition training
bull sharks. That's impossible.

24:54.547 --> 24:57.082
Impossible? Really?

24:57.084 --> 24:59.253
After what you just saw?

25:00.554 --> 25:02.955
How did you teach them
to swim in a formation?

25:02.957 --> 25:05.090
I'll explain everything
later, but first,

25:05.092 --> 25:07.592
please put on some
dry clothes, settle in,

25:07.594 --> 25:10.498
and we'll reconvene
in the wet lab in an hour.

25:15.969 --> 25:17.936
MISTY: You could get
incited for this.

25:17.938 --> 25:19.671
Relax, I'll talk to him.
Come on...

25:19.673 --> 25:21.174
Relax?

25:22.942 --> 25:25.078
One of your sharks
bit my foot.

25:25.912 --> 25:27.379
You're imagining things.

25:27.381 --> 25:29.180
AARON:
Look at my fricking shoe, dude.

25:29.182 --> 25:31.316
He has playing
with me, like...

25:31.318 --> 25:33.017
He was toying with me
or something.

25:33.019 --> 25:34.218
[LAUGHS]

25:34.220 --> 25:35.687
Sharks don't
play jokes, Aaron.

25:35.689 --> 25:39.557
You and I both know these
aren't normal sharks.

25:39.559 --> 25:43.160
Well, it's a good thing they
don't like the taste of nerds.

25:43.162 --> 25:44.595
Ha.

25:44.597 --> 25:47.931
FYI, this nerd keeps
this whole place running.

25:47.933 --> 25:51.238
[♪♪♪]

26:22.001 --> 26:23.270
[SIGHS]

26:48.027 --> 26:50.163
[♪♪♪]

27:25.732 --> 27:27.267
[SIGHS]

27:54.061 --> 27:56.030
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

27:58.164 --> 28:00.300
[SLURPING]

28:02.835 --> 28:04.771
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

28:07.007 --> 28:09.142
[PANTING, GASPING]

28:20.286 --> 28:22.055
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

28:26.160 --> 28:28.161
Come in.

28:38.205 --> 28:40.307
We have a problem.

28:43.343 --> 28:44.842
Wh-what's the problem?

28:44.844 --> 28:46.812
Sharks got out
this morning.

28:46.814 --> 28:48.280
What?

28:48.282 --> 28:51.082
Apparently, they dug a tunnel
under the electric fence.

28:51.084 --> 28:52.450
There was an accident.

28:52.452 --> 28:54.821
Trent thinks they may
have killed some fishermen.

28:56.690 --> 28:58.555
He thinks.

28:58.557 --> 29:00.190
He thinks.

29:00.192 --> 29:01.826
Meaning he didn't see it.

29:01.828 --> 29:04.731
He was concerned enough
to mention it to me.

29:07.500 --> 29:09.202
Okay.

29:10.470 --> 29:13.971
So the sharks
burrowed a tunnel

29:13.973 --> 29:15.273
under the electric fence,

29:15.275 --> 29:17.508
and then they followed
Trent back here.

29:17.510 --> 29:18.509
Yeah?

29:18.511 --> 29:19.846
Exactly.

29:21.247 --> 29:23.648
And do you know why?

29:23.650 --> 29:25.416
Because they're
problem solving.

29:25.418 --> 29:27.386
They're learning
how to learn,

29:27.388 --> 29:29.553
and they like it.

29:29.555 --> 29:32.890
Which means
the drugs are working.

29:32.892 --> 29:36.093
Each day, their
genetic structure evolves.

29:36.095 --> 29:39.630
My sharks are getting smarter.

29:39.632 --> 29:41.632
If it gets out
those sharks hurt someone,

29:41.634 --> 29:43.168
the liability
will be enormous.

29:43.170 --> 29:44.969
There's no coming back
from that kind of PR...

29:44.971 --> 29:47.537
The sharks are alive
because I allow them to be.

29:47.539 --> 29:49.073
Plain and simple.
I created them.

29:49.075 --> 29:52.444
And once my research is
completed, I will end them.

29:52.446 --> 29:55.179
What the f...
What does that mean?

29:55.181 --> 29:57.682
They have trackers
imbedded in their fins.

29:57.684 --> 30:00.084
We can always find them,
whether they're here,

30:00.086 --> 30:01.419
or out in the deep blue sea.

30:01.421 --> 30:04.354
And once
my experiment is over,

30:04.356 --> 30:06.691
I will simply kill them.

30:06.693 --> 30:10.530
All of them. So don't worry
about the liability.

30:13.299 --> 30:15.301
[WHISPERS]
There will be no evidence.

30:24.344 --> 30:25.478
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

30:50.069 --> 30:53.606
[♪♪♪]

31:07.254 --> 31:09.754
LESLIE:
How can you be hungry right now?

31:09.756 --> 31:13.158
Tsk. You know I eat
when I'm excited.

31:13.160 --> 31:15.026
So you aren't
having second thoughts?

31:15.028 --> 31:17.062
After Durant's
stunt out there?

31:17.064 --> 31:19.697
Yeah, he's...
eccentric.

31:19.699 --> 31:22.700
But his money's
still good.

31:22.702 --> 31:24.305
If you say so.

31:25.404 --> 31:27.974
Hey. Look at me.

31:29.308 --> 31:31.678
Babe, look at me.

31:34.581 --> 31:39.453
Look, we won't regret this.
I promise. Okay?

31:42.689 --> 31:47.059
But, um... There is
something I need to tell you.

31:47.061 --> 31:50.094
You're gonna
find out soon anyway.

31:50.096 --> 31:51.630
What is it?

31:51.632 --> 31:53.465
Ahem.

31:53.467 --> 31:54.865
I've been working
with Durant

31:54.867 --> 31:57.301
on the design
of his delivery molecules,

31:57.303 --> 31:58.669
making them smaller,

31:58.671 --> 32:01.706
so they effect DNA
structure more quickly.

32:01.708 --> 32:05.411
And... I also gave him access
to some of your work.

32:06.412 --> 32:08.446
I can't believe this.

32:08.448 --> 32:09.714
How long?

32:09.716 --> 32:10.948
Seven months.

32:10.950 --> 32:13.317
You've been lying to me
for seven months?

32:13.319 --> 32:15.953
No, not lying.
Just leaving something out.

32:15.955 --> 32:17.322
Why would you do that?

32:17.324 --> 32:18.823
I thought we were partners.

32:18.825 --> 32:20.224
We are partners.

32:20.226 --> 32:21.592
But I knew you'd be hesitant,

32:21.594 --> 32:23.461
because of Durant's
shady reputation.

32:23.463 --> 32:25.263
So you just decided
to go around me?

32:25.265 --> 32:26.796
Just to check it out.

32:26.798 --> 32:29.668
I mean, if this goes the way
I think it will, we'll be rich.

32:29.670 --> 32:32.370
I did not get into science
to get rich.

32:32.372 --> 32:36.040
Yeah, but with money
we can achieve so much more.

32:36.042 --> 32:39.613
No more groveling and
having to beg for grants.

32:43.216 --> 32:48.853
Look... You say the word,
and we can leave right now.

32:48.855 --> 32:50.690
I mean it.

32:52.959 --> 32:56.326
We're already out here.
I guess...

32:56.328 --> 32:58.463
I'm sorry.

32:58.465 --> 33:01.632
Don't ever do that again to me,
Daniel, I mean it.

33:01.634 --> 33:03.567
I need to trust you.

33:03.569 --> 33:06.571
I promise. All right?
We're a team.

33:06.573 --> 33:08.441
No more secrets.

33:12.178 --> 33:14.014
[♪♪♪]

33:23.690 --> 33:25.825
[BLOWTORCH SIZZLING SOFTLY]

33:34.401 --> 33:36.301
Please just stop
complaining about it.

33:36.303 --> 33:37.802
- It wasn't cool, man.
- You're fine.

33:37.804 --> 33:39.406
AARON:
It wasn't cool.

33:40.373 --> 33:41.872
Welcome!

33:41.874 --> 33:43.940
Welcome,
please come in.

33:43.942 --> 33:48.278
Now, I'm sure you're all curious
as to why I asked you here.

33:48.280 --> 33:50.383
Not everybody.

33:52.285 --> 33:54.252
So you finally told her.

33:54.254 --> 33:56.220
Ah. Yes.

33:56.222 --> 33:58.022
Good for you.

33:58.024 --> 34:01.459
Well, I've asked you here
because I need your help.

34:01.461 --> 34:04.364
I've reached a critical phase
in my research.

34:05.530 --> 34:08.033
Leslie,
if I may call you, Leslie,

34:08.034 --> 34:11.301
you and your husband study
traumatic brain injury?

34:11.303 --> 34:13.270
Among other things.

34:13.272 --> 34:15.005
And that includes
smart drugs?

34:15.007 --> 34:16.440
Nootropics.

34:16.442 --> 34:19.476
My company is one
of the leading producers

34:19.478 --> 34:21.779
of biopharma drugs,
including...

34:21.781 --> 34:24.081
Performance enhancers.

34:24.083 --> 34:27.951
You've been sanctioned by
the World Anti-Doping Agency.

34:27.953 --> 34:32.623
In this case, intelligence
enhancers, Nootropics.

34:32.625 --> 34:35.259
You're talking about drugs
like Adderall?

34:35.261 --> 34:38.129
Well Nootropics can
improve memory access,

34:38.130 --> 34:41.933
increase concentration, even
speed up your decision making.

34:41.935 --> 34:43.567
So basically just stimulants?

34:43.569 --> 34:44.768
That's right.

34:44.770 --> 34:47.408
Nothing can increase
native intelligence.

34:48.206 --> 34:49.607
Until now.

34:49.609 --> 34:53.277
You see,
I've developed compounds

34:53.279 --> 34:58.082
that can actually alter the
genetic structure of the brain.

34:58.084 --> 34:59.250
Speeding up evolution

34:59.252 --> 35:02.319
in the direction
of greater intelligence.

35:02.321 --> 35:03.554
Much greater.

35:03.556 --> 35:06.723
And we deliver these compounds,

35:06.725 --> 35:10.629
using targeted antibodies.

35:10.631 --> 35:12.466
From sharks.

35:13.634 --> 35:15.669
You're testing
these drugs on sharks?

35:16.803 --> 35:19.473
That's absolutely inhumane.

35:20.806 --> 35:24.408
It's not inhumane at all.
Let me show you.

35:24.410 --> 35:26.377
- Aaron.
- Trent,

35:26.379 --> 35:27.948
we're ready for Bella.

35:31.718 --> 35:33.384
[HI-PITCH WHISTLE]

35:33.386 --> 35:35.721
[♪♪♪]

35:57.877 --> 35:59.611
TRENT:
All right, she's out.

35:59.613 --> 36:01.645
- [KEYBOARD CLACKS]
- They got her.

36:01.647 --> 36:03.950
[BEEPS, WATER RELEASES]

36:32.446 --> 36:34.078
Easy, easy, easy.

36:34.080 --> 36:35.082
All right.

36:36.348 --> 36:37.848
Mike, you got her?

36:37.850 --> 36:39.884
Aren't you scared,
being that close?

36:39.886 --> 36:41.889
Nah. Sharks don't worry me.

36:48.627 --> 36:50.527
JOSH:
Vitals are online.

36:50.529 --> 36:53.864
BP 34 over 68.

36:53.866 --> 36:56.967
Heart rate 42 bpm.

36:56.969 --> 37:00.471
Respiration rate
and oxygen levels steady.

37:00.473 --> 37:02.373
She's looking good.

37:02.375 --> 37:08.312
As you can see, our treatment of
our sharks is totally painless.

37:08.314 --> 37:11.915
If we bind a drug
on a molecular level

37:11.917 --> 37:13.618
to the shark's antibodies,

37:13.620 --> 37:16.120
we can then mainline that drug

37:16.122 --> 37:18.355
to whatever area
of the brain we want.

37:18.357 --> 37:21.759
We've already increased
Bella's base intelligence

37:21.761 --> 37:23.226
by a thousand-fold.

37:23.228 --> 37:24.895
And you actually think
you can get

37:24.897 --> 37:26.563
the same results
in human beings?

37:26.565 --> 37:30.234
I think
it's an absolute necessity

37:30.236 --> 37:34.775
if we want to maintain
the supremacy of mankind.

37:36.741 --> 37:41.913
DURANT: Artificial intelligence
is becoming stronger every year.

37:41.915 --> 37:44.248
Soon, quantum computing
will begin

37:44.250 --> 37:47.652
an exponential
acceleration of the ability

37:47.654 --> 37:50.888
of our computers
to teach themselves.

37:50.890 --> 37:54.591
And when that happens,
we'll lose control of them,

37:54.593 --> 37:57.997
and our world, in an instant.

38:00.632 --> 38:02.703
DURANT:
Man himself...

38:04.270 --> 38:06.206
will become obsolete.

38:07.707 --> 38:12.379
And they will...
destroy us.

38:14.781 --> 38:17.348
But there's another way.

38:17.350 --> 38:22.719
The human brain has a hundred
billion neurons.

38:22.721 --> 38:26.390
Our potential is greater
than any machine.

38:26.392 --> 38:29.326
It just needs to be...

38:29.328 --> 38:31.060
unleashed.

38:31.062 --> 38:34.133
So you're the savior
of the entire human race?

38:35.535 --> 38:37.404
I think you've
got a God complex.

38:39.504 --> 38:43.007
When I'm successful,

38:43.009 --> 38:45.779
we can all be gods.

38:46.846 --> 38:48.381
Or monsters.

38:49.515 --> 38:52.018
[♪♪♪]

38:58.957 --> 39:01.225
You realize that it was
much of your research

39:01.227 --> 39:03.560
that helped lead me
in the proper direction

39:03.562 --> 39:04.797
in the first place?

39:15.442 --> 39:18.241
Is your boss always
such a piece of work?

39:18.243 --> 39:21.245
He just started taking
the new drugs himself.

39:21.247 --> 39:23.313
They seem to kinda
hop him up.

39:23.315 --> 39:25.016
It's not exactly a secret.

39:25.018 --> 39:28.419
He's administering the drugs
to himself? That's insane.

39:28.421 --> 39:31.755
Dude built a multi-billion
dollar empire out of nothing.

39:31.757 --> 39:34.125
And he's a scientific genius.

39:34.127 --> 39:36.697
Who am I to tell him
what to do?

39:38.397 --> 39:39.466
Look, it happened.

39:41.134 --> 39:43.667
Have you noticed any negative
side effects on the sharks

39:43.669 --> 39:45.703
from these so-called
wonder-drugs?

39:45.705 --> 39:47.538
I wouldn't call
them negative.

39:47.540 --> 39:49.073
Her eyesight
has improved.

39:49.075 --> 39:50.975
And she seems to be
able to communicate

39:50.977 --> 39:52.375
with the other bulls.

39:52.377 --> 39:55.314
- You're kidding?
- Nope, I'm not.

40:01.353 --> 40:03.754
So what's going on here?

40:03.756 --> 40:06.158
[♪♪♪]

40:12.598 --> 40:14.067
[ELECTRICITY HUMMING]

40:24.511 --> 40:27.111
You know, I'm not really sure
why you brought me here.

40:27.113 --> 40:29.513
What exactly
are you expecting of me?

40:29.515 --> 40:33.083
Well Bella's been displaying
some unusual behaviors

40:33.085 --> 40:35.219
that don't seem
to be directly related

40:35.221 --> 40:37.855
to her increased intelligence.

40:37.857 --> 40:40.326
I was hoping that
you could tell us why.

40:42.428 --> 40:43.997
She's pregnant.

40:46.366 --> 40:48.199
What?

40:48.201 --> 40:51.601
That's impossible. I do blood
draws on her every week.

40:51.603 --> 40:53.237
We'd know if she
was knocked-up.

40:53.239 --> 40:54.875
Did you do an ultrasound?

40:56.843 --> 40:59.611
I've been swimming with sharks
since I was 7 years old.

40:59.613 --> 41:01.612
I know a knocked-up
shark when I see one.

41:01.614 --> 41:05.683
Why wouldn't this show up
on her hormone panels?

41:05.685 --> 41:07.484
You said your drugs

41:07.486 --> 41:09.152
alter her DNA.

41:09.154 --> 41:11.422
Maybe they do more to her
than you thought.

41:11.424 --> 41:12.723
[CONSOLE BEEPING]

41:12.725 --> 41:14.361
- It's possible.
- AARON: Hey Trent?

41:23.569 --> 41:25.505
What the hell?

41:32.944 --> 41:34.547
You might be right.

41:35.948 --> 41:38.118
I should have
seen this myself.

41:39.551 --> 41:42.454
Maybe you were too busy patting
yourself on the back.

41:44.556 --> 41:45.989
Possibly.

41:45.991 --> 41:48.926
[♪♪♪]

41:48.928 --> 41:51.230
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

42:10.815 --> 42:13.219
[HI-PITCHED WHISTLE ]

42:29.368 --> 42:31.304
[BANGING]

42:50.857 --> 42:52.058
[LOCK CLICKS]

42:56.261 --> 42:58.830
The gen's been damaged.
The boat slammed up against it.

42:58.832 --> 43:01.366
And on top of that,
there's a couple hundred gallons

43:01.368 --> 43:03.636
- of fuel in the lagoon.
- What the hell, man?

43:12.078 --> 43:15.179
What happens if the fuel
hits the electric fence?

43:15.181 --> 43:18.582
We've got oxygen tanks stored
in the underwater bin.

43:18.584 --> 43:20.219
Yeah, I know.

43:40.973 --> 43:42.975
Gotta get a throat culture.

44:06.332 --> 44:07.897
- [SHARK GROWLS]
- Oh, shit!

44:07.899 --> 44:09.632
[SNAPS]

44:09.634 --> 44:11.236
[ALL YELLING]

44:20.446 --> 44:21.779
JOSH:
Jesus Christ!

44:21.781 --> 44:24.114
She was supposed
to be out for another hour!

44:24.116 --> 44:25.549
Is Bella all right?

44:25.551 --> 44:26.716
Yes, she's fine.

44:26.718 --> 44:28.453
- Are you sure?
- Yes!

44:28.455 --> 44:31.123
And I'm fine too,
thanks for asking!

44:33.725 --> 44:35.993
[RUMBLING]

44:35.995 --> 44:37.294
What was that?

44:37.296 --> 44:41.832
[POP MUSIC FAINTLY PLAYING
OVER HEADPHONES]

44:41.834 --> 44:45.703
BURNS: <i>"Mr. Durant has been displaying
increasingly erratic behavior,</i>

44:45.705 --> 44:48.438
<i>"and questionable judgment,
ever since he began</i>

44:48.440 --> 44:50.241
<i>"his nootropic regimen.</i>

44:50.243 --> 44:52.509
<i>I have repeatedly
advised him against..."</i>

44:52.511 --> 44:53.712
[BANG]

44:56.582 --> 44:57.616
[GRUNTS]

44:59.518 --> 45:00.687
[YELLS]

45:04.223 --> 45:08.260
[SIREN WAILING]

45:10.596 --> 45:12.862
[BEEPING]

45:12.864 --> 45:14.464
LESLIE:
Oh! What is it?

45:14.466 --> 45:18.201
Oh my G...
What's going on?

45:18.203 --> 45:20.140
- What was that?
- I don't know.

45:21.040 --> 45:22.839
LESLIE [GASPS]:
Oh, my God.

45:22.841 --> 45:24.544
What the hell is happening?

45:28.814 --> 45:31.315
MISTY: Does that mean
the fence is down?

45:31.317 --> 45:32.815
Yeah, only partly.

45:32.817 --> 45:34.850
- What do you mean only partly?
- I mean I can fix it!

45:34.852 --> 45:37.489
- Was that an explosion?
- This whole place is on fire.

45:38.556 --> 45:40.857
- Is that Bella?
- Yeah, she's the red one.

45:40.859 --> 45:43.661
Does... Does she normally
separate herself from...

45:43.663 --> 45:45.862
No, Dr. Calhoun,
she does not!

45:45.864 --> 45:49.334
[GROANING, PANTING]

45:58.277 --> 45:59.609
[MUTTERS]

45:59.611 --> 46:01.447
What the...

46:02.915 --> 46:04.216
Hello?

46:05.151 --> 46:07.051
[SHIP CREAKING]

46:07.053 --> 46:08.321
[GRUNTS]

46:15.194 --> 46:16.659
JOSH:
Oh, shit...

46:16.661 --> 46:19.562
No, no, no! Come on,
you gotta be kidding me!

46:19.564 --> 46:21.165
She's taking out the cameras.

46:21.167 --> 46:22.498
She can do that?

46:22.500 --> 46:25.205
[SHIP CONTINUES CREAKING]

46:36.181 --> 46:37.584
What the heck?

46:42.555 --> 46:43.589
[GRUNTING]

46:50.995 --> 46:53.499
[YELLING]

46:57.904 --> 47:00.170
Damn it! Hull integrity
has been breached!

47:00.172 --> 47:03.107
TRENT: Release the pressure so
we don't lose the wet pool.

47:03.109 --> 47:04.310
You got it.

47:06.210 --> 47:08.814
[♪♪♪]

47:10.882 --> 47:12.618
This corridor is flooding!

47:13.986 --> 47:15.421
MIKE:
This is trouble.

47:22.761 --> 47:23.926
[♪♪♪]

47:23.928 --> 47:25.196
Aah!

47:25.198 --> 47:26.933
What is it?

47:30.002 --> 47:31.067
[GASPING]

47:31.069 --> 47:32.437
[GROANS, COUGHS]

47:33.772 --> 47:35.038
[GAGS]

47:35.040 --> 47:37.708
Did you see that? Those
sharks tore Craig to pieces.

47:37.710 --> 47:40.444
I've never seen a shark-bite
pattern like that before.

47:40.446 --> 47:42.312
We're all gonna die,
aren't we?

47:42.314 --> 47:44.080
No, we're not.
Everybody calm down.

47:44.082 --> 47:45.549
Aaron.
Aaron, what's our status?

47:45.551 --> 47:47.051
This is bad.
This is really bad.

47:47.053 --> 47:50.087
Aaron! Hull status.
Are there multiple breaches?

47:50.089 --> 47:53.056
Only the eastern
corridor... so far.

47:53.058 --> 47:55.759
Don't say "so far."
Why would you say that?

47:55.761 --> 47:58.094
I've never seen
them act this way.

47:58.096 --> 47:59.797
They're in a frenzy.

47:59.799 --> 48:02.933
Can you please tell me a frenzy
isn't as bad as it sounds?

48:02.935 --> 48:05.136
It means they're in serious
hunting mode.

48:05.138 --> 48:06.937
This is so messed up.

48:06.939 --> 48:10.007
That's why they aren't leaving,
even though the fence is down...

48:10.009 --> 48:11.674
They're all staying to get us?

48:11.676 --> 48:14.877
Wait a minute, wait a minute!
This doesn't make sense.

48:14.879 --> 48:17.913
If all the sharks
are out in the lagoon,

48:17.915 --> 48:20.285
who did that to Craig?

48:26.359 --> 48:30.192
I know I told you not to backup
any of my research in the cloud,

48:30.194 --> 48:31.295
but now you have to.

48:31.297 --> 48:33.063
I can't.

48:33.065 --> 48:35.901
Even if I wanted to,
whole system's gone down.

48:37.636 --> 48:38.937
MISTY:
Oh, my God...

48:47.180 --> 48:48.478
I figured it out.

48:48.480 --> 48:50.015
Figured what out?

48:54.352 --> 48:55.621
What's happening?

48:57.957 --> 48:59.025
What is it?
Spit it out.

49:00.393 --> 49:01.993
Bella isn't pregnant anymore.

49:01.995 --> 49:03.159
What?

49:03.161 --> 49:04.663
She had her babies.

49:06.064 --> 49:09.268
The drop into the wet pool
must have triggered labor.

49:11.169 --> 49:14.737
Whatever you crated here,
Durant, is vicious.

49:14.739 --> 49:17.973
These aren't
your typical sharks.

49:17.975 --> 49:21.712
They're just teeth and muscle
and killer instinct.

49:21.714 --> 49:24.882
It's the only thing that can
explain what happened to Craig.

49:24.884 --> 49:28.421
You're talking like they're
a bunch of super-piranha.

49:29.154 --> 49:30.790
They're worse.

49:32.058 --> 49:33.493
Much worse.

49:35.460 --> 49:37.863
[SCREECHING]

49:39.265 --> 49:41.600
[SHARKS SCREECHING]

49:44.469 --> 49:46.805
[MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY]

49:48.373 --> 49:50.507
- Look at me. Daniel.
- We can use this one...

49:50.509 --> 49:52.141
Daniel, look at me!

49:52.143 --> 49:54.210
[BOTH PANTING]

49:54.212 --> 49:56.716
Okay, breathe, baby.
Breathe.

50:02.288 --> 50:04.791
- I love you.
- I love you, too.

50:07.460 --> 50:09.460
We're gonna get
through this.

50:09.462 --> 50:11.064
- We are.
- Yeah, okay.

50:13.198 --> 50:15.534
Come on. Come on.

50:20.372 --> 50:21.938
[CLANGING]

50:21.940 --> 50:24.741
Will you two please
settle down.

50:24.743 --> 50:27.210
There's no benefit
to losing our heads.

50:27.212 --> 50:28.444
Aren't you the one
who said

50:28.446 --> 50:30.714
your security system
is infallible?

50:30.716 --> 50:32.181
Yeah,
it should've been.

50:32.183 --> 50:33.583
Obviously,
my work has been

50:33.585 --> 50:35.618
even more successful
than I thought.

50:35.620 --> 50:37.154
[LAUGHS BITTERLY]

50:37.156 --> 50:39.859
If this is success,
I'd love to see failure.

50:41.393 --> 50:43.259
We need to get
topside.

50:43.261 --> 50:44.795
I agree.

50:44.797 --> 50:46.962
There's just one
problem.

50:46.964 --> 50:49.565
All the exits are
underwater.

50:49.567 --> 50:52.236
[♪♪♪]

50:52.238 --> 50:54.904
Maybe they don't realize
there's a hole in the fence?

50:54.906 --> 50:56.774
They know it's there,
they created it.

50:56.776 --> 50:58.375
Why aren't they leaving?
Misty?

50:58.377 --> 51:00.409
There's something here
they still want.

51:00.411 --> 51:02.480
Yeah, us.

51:02.482 --> 51:05.181
You wanna know why chimps
are so dangerous?

51:05.183 --> 51:07.650
Because they're smart enough
to hold a grudge!

51:07.652 --> 51:10.853
Just like humans!
I mean, that's it, right?

51:10.855 --> 51:13.957
It's gotta be.
Bella's not only smart,

51:13.959 --> 51:15.991
she's mean
and she wants us dead!

51:15.993 --> 51:19.129
The rest are her soldiers!
They'll do whatever she wants!

51:19.131 --> 51:21.098
We are screwed!
We are so screwed!

51:21.100 --> 51:23.632
Okay. We don't have time
for theories or meltdowns.

51:23.634 --> 51:25.701
We gotta figure out a way
to get out of here.

51:25.703 --> 51:27.670
Is there a way
to make a phone call...

51:27.672 --> 51:30.040
- Like, a satellite phone?
- It only works topside.

51:30.042 --> 51:33.176
More of our fearless leader's
fanatical trade-secret bullshit

51:33.178 --> 51:36.179
that puts everyone else
in danger because he's nuts!

51:36.181 --> 51:38.714
- What did you say?
- I said, fuck you!

51:38.716 --> 51:41.984
What are you gonna do, huh?
Fire me? I quit!

51:41.986 --> 51:44.620
So how do we get out of here
if there's no exit?

51:44.622 --> 51:46.790
There is one other way.

51:46.792 --> 51:48.491
You thinking
what I'm thinking?

51:48.493 --> 51:51.462
- Wet pool.
- Heh, heh! Wait, wait...

51:51.464 --> 51:53.330
You want us
to swim out of here?

51:53.332 --> 51:55.966
No way in hell, dude.
I'm not getting in the water

51:55.968 --> 51:58.134
with those sharks again!
No! Uh-uh! End of.

51:58.136 --> 52:00.337
Yeah, no, Daniel and I
are not comfortable

52:00.339 --> 52:01.607
- with that either.
- No.

52:02.573 --> 52:04.540
You don't have
to swim.

52:04.542 --> 52:06.878
So what? We teleport?

52:07.779 --> 52:09.913
Mike can ride
the DPV

52:09.915 --> 52:11.047
to the main hub,

52:11.049 --> 52:14.851
call the Coast Guard
on the topside SAT.

52:14.853 --> 52:15.919
We get help.

52:15.921 --> 52:18.288
Yes, please,
I'm a big fan of help.

52:18.290 --> 52:21.725
Yeah, maybe you forgot
about the baby sharks?

52:21.727 --> 52:23.127
A little important
detail there.

52:23.129 --> 52:24.862
They must have come in
with the hull breach.

52:24.864 --> 52:26.763
They've found food in here,
so they'll probably

52:26.765 --> 52:29.766
stick around in here,
for a while at least.

52:29.768 --> 52:32.101
All right,
it's a solid plan,

52:32.103 --> 52:33.370
only I'll go.

52:33.372 --> 52:35.371
No, you won't.
You're needed here.

52:35.373 --> 52:36.908
MISTY:
No, I'll go.

52:39.544 --> 52:41.245
- No way.
- I'm going.

52:41.247 --> 52:43.212
No. It's too dangerous
and this is my job.

52:43.214 --> 52:44.982
I'm going whether
you like it or not.

52:44.984 --> 52:47.083
- No need to risk your life.
- It's my life to risk.

52:47.085 --> 52:49.185
MIKE: We can't afford
to lose us all!

52:49.187 --> 52:52.522
Besides, I'm South African,
I live for this crazy shit!

52:52.524 --> 52:55.025
Those sharks can suck
my ass!

52:55.027 --> 52:57.530
TRENT:
Mike, wait! Mike!

52:58.830 --> 53:01.267
- Mike!
- MISTY: Here we go!

53:05.738 --> 53:07.536
DANIEL:
Does anybody see him?

53:07.538 --> 53:10.739
- LESLIE: Where'd he go?
- DANIEL: Does anybody see him?

53:10.741 --> 53:12.509
- Where is he?
- There he is.

53:12.511 --> 53:13.877
AARON:
I see him.

53:13.879 --> 53:15.377
Do you think
he's gonna make it?

53:15.379 --> 53:16.580
Yes.

53:16.582 --> 53:18.013
AARON:
Oh, shit, there's a shark.

53:18.015 --> 53:20.552
- ALL [OVERLAPPING]: Mike!
- LESLIE: Mike, behind you!

53:21.786 --> 53:23.853
[MUFFLED THUD]

53:23.855 --> 53:26.158
- [ALL EXCLAIM]
- LESLIE: Oh, my God!

53:27.625 --> 53:29.125
- Oh, no! Mike!
- Is he dead?

53:29.127 --> 53:31.127
- AARON: He's not moving.
- JOSH: He's out.

53:31.129 --> 53:33.862
LESLIE: This is not happening.
This isn't happening!

53:33.864 --> 53:35.732
This isn't...
This is....

53:35.734 --> 53:37.602
[LESLIE PANTING]

53:39.303 --> 53:42.306
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

53:42.308 --> 53:44.010
[LESLIE PANTING]

53:50.049 --> 53:51.651
Come on, Trent.

53:53.919 --> 53:57.286
- He's got him. He's got him.
- He's gonna be okay.

53:57.288 --> 54:00.792
AARON: He's coming to the wet pool,
he's coming to the wet pool!

54:03.129 --> 54:05.228
Come on, come on,
come on, come on!

54:05.230 --> 54:07.933
- Can't see them.
- Where are they?

54:09.701 --> 54:11.801
JOSH:
Pull them up! Pull them up!

54:11.803 --> 54:14.306
[ALL EXCLAIMING]

54:17.642 --> 54:19.678
[GRUNTING]

54:21.513 --> 54:23.616
Give her room!
Give her room.

54:24.448 --> 54:26.248
[♪♪♪]

54:26.250 --> 54:27.886
[PANTING]

54:34.393 --> 54:35.725
[EXHALES]

54:35.727 --> 54:38.027
JOSH:
Come on, Mike! Come on, man.

54:38.029 --> 54:40.166
[PANTING]
Come on, Mike!

54:44.502 --> 54:46.305
God damn it, come on!

54:50.009 --> 54:52.341
[SIGHS SHARPLY]
Come on!

54:52.343 --> 54:53.743
- [RETCHES]
- [GASPS]

54:53.745 --> 54:55.612
Got him!
I got him! I got him!

54:55.614 --> 54:57.214
- [RETCHES]
- Got him!

54:57.216 --> 54:59.382
[MIKE COUGHING]

54:59.384 --> 55:00.583
[PANTING]

55:00.585 --> 55:01.850
What happened?

55:01.852 --> 55:04.554
You got blindsided
by a shark.

55:04.556 --> 55:06.022
You were dead, bro.

55:06.024 --> 55:08.793
I knew I should have gone
and watched your six.

55:09.895 --> 55:11.562
MIKE:
I told you...

55:11.564 --> 55:14.230
Those sharks
can kiss my ass...

55:14.232 --> 55:15.498
[ROARS]

55:15.500 --> 55:17.736
[ALL SCREAMING]

55:19.837 --> 55:22.707
[♪♪♪]

55:28.145 --> 55:30.781
Do we have any more
weapons?

55:30.783 --> 55:33.183
Bang-sticks, spear-guns,

55:33.185 --> 55:34.250
strychnine nitrate?

55:34.252 --> 55:36.386
Okay, calm down.
Everybody calm down.

55:36.388 --> 55:38.455
I've got flares on the boat.
That's about it.

55:38.457 --> 55:40.656
You don't...
You don't mean this, all right?

55:40.658 --> 55:44.129
Now, you... You've spent your
entire life protecting sharks.

55:45.997 --> 55:47.730
I help people see

55:47.732 --> 55:49.766
that sharks aren't monsters.

55:49.768 --> 55:51.701
But your sharks?

55:51.703 --> 55:55.404
You've turned them
into monsters!

55:55.406 --> 55:58.341
We cannot let these sharks

55:58.343 --> 55:59.909
leave this complex!

55:59.911 --> 56:01.911
We cannot let them
keep breeding!

56:01.913 --> 56:05.281
We cannot let them
hurt any more people!

56:05.283 --> 56:07.917
We have to kill
those fucking sharks!

56:07.919 --> 56:09.719
All right,
but you are ignoring

56:09.721 --> 56:11.620
the very valuable research

56:11.622 --> 56:12.922
that they are enabling.

56:12.924 --> 56:14.190
Listen, listen,

56:14.192 --> 56:17.426
I am so close
to a breakthrough

56:17.428 --> 56:19.797
that will change
the course of history!

56:19.799 --> 56:22.900
[LAUGHING] Excuse me, but you
might wanna tell that to Mike.

56:22.902 --> 56:24.400
Oh, no, wait,
you can't.

56:24.402 --> 56:27.703
You wanna know why?
Because a shark ate his head!

56:27.705 --> 56:29.873
[♪♪♪]

56:29.875 --> 56:32.011
[METAL CREAKING]

56:33.245 --> 56:35.411
We're losing pressure
control.

56:35.413 --> 56:37.446
What does that mean?

56:37.448 --> 56:40.583
- It means it's gonna blow!
- [EXPLOSION]

56:40.585 --> 56:42.888
[ALL SCREAMING]

56:49.194 --> 56:50.161
[EXPLOSION]

56:57.968 --> 56:59.871
[MUFFLED EXPLOSION]

57:00.973 --> 57:03.109
[SCREAMING]

57:06.477 --> 57:08.012
DANIEL:
Leslie!

57:09.415 --> 57:11.681
[SCREAMING]

57:11.683 --> 57:12.681
[THUD]

57:12.683 --> 57:15.118
- Leslie!
- [SIGHS]

57:15.120 --> 57:17.256
LESLIE [SCREAMING]:
Daniel!

57:18.189 --> 57:20.991
Push.
Come on, come on!

57:20.993 --> 57:22.625
- [MISTY PANTING]
- Come on!

57:22.627 --> 57:25.629
- There's too much water!
- Help me, don't give up on me!

57:25.631 --> 57:27.230
- I can't...
- Push!

57:27.232 --> 57:29.431
- [MISTY GROANING]
- Right here.

57:29.433 --> 57:30.701
Ha! I got it!

57:30.703 --> 57:32.569
- Good!
- I got it! I got it!

57:32.571 --> 57:34.737
- You okay?
- Yeah. Are you?

57:34.739 --> 57:37.475
- Yeah... Jesus.
- [PANTING]

57:42.080 --> 57:44.279
Are the different sections
of this complex

57:44.281 --> 57:45.915
sealed away
from each other?

57:45.917 --> 57:47.683
You wanna know
if the baby sharks

57:47.685 --> 57:49.185
are locked
in the Eastern Corridor.

57:49.187 --> 57:51.654
Yeah, it'd be nice
if they were.

57:51.656 --> 57:53.022
No luck.

57:53.024 --> 57:54.757
They could be anywhere.

57:54.759 --> 57:56.896
[PANTING]

57:59.464 --> 58:02.799
How the hell did you end up
working for this guy?

58:02.801 --> 58:04.500
He's out of his mind.

58:04.502 --> 58:08.270
Yeah, only since he started
taking those drugs himself.

58:08.272 --> 58:11.473
He was an asshole before,
but not like this.

58:11.475 --> 58:14.279
I should have quit
this job months ago.

58:15.948 --> 58:17.482
So why are you
still here?

58:19.283 --> 58:20.986
Why are <i>you</i> here?

58:22.921 --> 58:24.823
[METAL CREAKING]

58:25.756 --> 58:28.259
[♪♪♪]

58:31.830 --> 58:33.866
[MISTY PANTING]

58:36.968 --> 58:39.337
Do you know
where we're going?

58:45.009 --> 58:47.145
Is there a way out?

58:48.846 --> 58:50.982
Let's hope
it's not flooded.

58:52.149 --> 58:54.419
MISTY:
Yeah, let's hope.

59:10.935 --> 59:13.072
[♪♪♪]

59:18.777 --> 59:19.942
Leslie!

59:19.944 --> 59:21.947
[GRUNTING]

59:23.147 --> 59:24.614
"Come to Cape Town,"
they said.

59:24.616 --> 59:26.716
- "It'll be fun," they said!
- Keep it down.

59:26.718 --> 59:29.451
Remind me why we're going
to the crew's quarters again.

59:29.453 --> 59:31.554
It's the farthest thing away
from the eastern corridor.

59:31.556 --> 59:34.324
I get that, but shouldn't
we be looking for the others?

59:34.326 --> 59:36.225
Dude, Bella's babies
are on the prowl.

59:36.227 --> 59:38.194
We need to get out
of this water.

59:38.196 --> 59:40.830
I get that but my gut's saying
there's safety in numbers.

59:40.832 --> 59:43.933
Yeah? Well, my gut's telling me
we need to find a way out.

59:43.935 --> 59:46.169
Look, Aaron.
Do not make me do this alone.

59:46.171 --> 59:49.304
Please, man. Come on.

59:49.306 --> 59:51.875
All right, but you better
be right about this.

59:51.877 --> 59:53.344
This way.

59:54.846 --> 59:56.982
[♪♪♪]

01:00:07.524 --> 01:00:09.394
Leslie!

01:00:13.564 --> 01:00:15.533
[SHARKS SCREECHING]

01:00:18.270 --> 01:00:21.270
AARON:
We're gonna be fine.

01:00:21.272 --> 01:00:23.339
How can you be
so optimistic right now?

01:00:23.341 --> 01:00:25.107
I'm clinging to hope,
dude.

01:00:25.109 --> 01:00:27.844
It's a desperate cling, yeah,
but it's still a cling.

01:00:27.846 --> 01:00:31.815
There's the crew's quarters.
I think we'll be safe in there.

01:00:31.817 --> 01:00:33.283
I don't know, man,
I still think

01:00:33.285 --> 01:00:35.152
we gotta be finding
a way out of here.

01:00:35.154 --> 01:00:36.553
Dude, we're walking
fish food.

01:00:36.555 --> 01:00:38.321
We need to get away
from the sharks

01:00:38.323 --> 01:00:39.957
and just wait
for help to come.

01:00:39.959 --> 01:00:41.857
Yeah, and what if
it doesn't come, Josh?

01:00:41.859 --> 01:00:44.027
So much for clinging
to hope.

01:00:44.029 --> 01:00:45.527
By the way,

01:00:45.529 --> 01:00:48.897
if I ever ask you for
a job again, just ignore me.

01:00:48.899 --> 01:00:51.703
AARON: Dude, you were living
in your mom's basement.

01:00:53.004 --> 01:00:54.473
Come on.

01:01:02.980 --> 01:01:05.116
[♪♪♪]

01:01:24.169 --> 01:01:25.770
[ELECTRONIC BEEP]

01:01:29.774 --> 01:01:31.377
[RATTLING]

01:01:38.683 --> 01:01:40.683
[PILLS RATTLE]

01:01:40.685 --> 01:01:42.688
[GRUNTING]

01:01:45.656 --> 01:01:47.188
[METAL RUMBLING]

01:01:47.190 --> 01:01:48.727
<i>[CRACKLING]</i>

01:02:06.611 --> 01:02:07.976
Hey!

01:02:07.978 --> 01:02:09.415
Where is everybody?

01:02:10.580 --> 01:02:12.681
[PANTING]
Haven't seen a soul.

01:02:12.683 --> 01:02:15.819
Everyone must have scattered
through different exits.

01:02:15.821 --> 01:02:17.853
You scared,
Durant?

01:02:17.855 --> 01:02:19.754
Be a fool not to be.

01:02:19.756 --> 01:02:22.424
Well, it ain't no fun
when the rabbit's got the gun.

01:02:22.426 --> 01:02:24.127
- Is it?
- How about we focus

01:02:24.129 --> 01:02:25.761
on getting out of here?

01:02:25.763 --> 01:02:27.496
How?
We're sealed in.

01:02:27.498 --> 01:02:30.098
If we can make it
to the filtration room,

01:02:30.100 --> 01:02:31.902
we should be able
to climb out

01:02:31.904 --> 01:02:33.603
- through the air shaft.
- How?

01:02:33.605 --> 01:02:37.272
They put in access rungs
to facilitate maintenance.

01:02:37.274 --> 01:02:40.243
Oh, good,
didn't know about that.

01:02:40.245 --> 01:02:41.877
It's a good thing
I'm here, isn't it?

01:02:41.879 --> 01:02:44.380
- We need to find the others.
- I know...

01:02:44.382 --> 01:02:46.283
and we will,
but we gotta get topside

01:02:46.285 --> 01:02:48.784
and call for help first.
If there's another hull breach,

01:02:48.786 --> 01:02:51.288
this whole thing
is gonna be underwater.

01:02:51.290 --> 01:02:53.656
Trent's right...

01:02:53.658 --> 01:02:57.594
Don't agree with me.
Makes me nervous.

01:02:57.596 --> 01:02:59.062
Is he right?

01:02:59.064 --> 01:03:00.763
I don't know.

01:03:00.765 --> 01:03:04.000
It's the best option we got.
Let's move.

01:03:04.002 --> 01:03:06.171
[♪♪♪]

01:03:10.975 --> 01:03:12.975
Leslie!

01:03:12.977 --> 01:03:15.213
Can you hear me?

01:03:20.518 --> 01:03:22.317
Leslie, where are you?

01:03:22.319 --> 01:03:24.422
[SHARKS SCREECHING]

01:03:31.029 --> 01:03:33.094
- [PANTING]
- [SHARKS SHRIEKING]

01:03:33.096 --> 01:03:35.263
[♪♪♪]

01:03:35.265 --> 01:03:37.802
[GRUNTING, YELLING]

01:03:46.712 --> 01:03:48.647
[SCREECHING]

01:04:01.725 --> 01:04:04.262
The filtration room's
this way.

01:04:16.908 --> 01:04:18.944
[♪♪♪]

01:04:45.669 --> 01:04:46.938
[GASPS]

01:05:05.522 --> 01:05:07.858
Let's get
this door closed.

01:05:10.261 --> 01:05:11.661
Come on.

01:05:11.663 --> 01:05:13.395
God damn it,
Aaron,

01:05:13.397 --> 01:05:15.498
I told you to get
this goddamned door fixed!

01:05:15.500 --> 01:05:16.665
Yeah, Josh,
it's not like

01:05:16.667 --> 01:05:19.268
I haven't been busy
the last 24 hours.

01:05:19.270 --> 01:05:21.640
[SHARKS SCREECHING]

01:05:22.506 --> 01:05:24.475
Did you hear that?

01:05:26.076 --> 01:05:28.013
[SCREECHING INTENSIFIES]

01:05:29.714 --> 01:05:31.848
- Oh, God.
- Why did you say, "Oh, God?"

01:05:31.850 --> 01:05:34.283
- Get away from the door, Josh!
- Shit!

01:05:34.285 --> 01:05:37.085
[SCREECHING]

01:05:37.087 --> 01:05:38.920
[GRUNTS]

01:05:38.922 --> 01:05:41.324
[GASPS]

01:05:41.326 --> 01:05:43.292
AARON:
Dude! Get out of there, man!

01:05:43.294 --> 01:05:45.430
[PANTING]

01:05:47.198 --> 01:05:49.799
AARON: Oh, you gotta be
freaking kidding me!

01:05:49.801 --> 01:05:52.601
Josh! Josh!

01:05:52.603 --> 01:05:54.737
[SHARKS SCREECHING]

01:05:54.739 --> 01:05:56.875
This is so not
how I wanna die.

01:06:10.120 --> 01:06:11.886
[PANTING]

01:06:11.888 --> 01:06:13.724
[THUDDING]

01:06:16.160 --> 01:06:19.161
[LOUD CRASH, CREAKING]

01:06:19.163 --> 01:06:20.931
Oh, God...

01:06:23.435 --> 01:06:25.400
[SCREECHING]

01:06:25.402 --> 01:06:28.237
No!
Aaron! Aaron!

01:06:28.239 --> 01:06:29.804
No!

01:06:29.806 --> 01:06:33.042
- [MUFFLED] No! No!
- Josh?

01:06:33.044 --> 01:06:34.310
No...

01:06:34.312 --> 01:06:35.812
Josh?

01:06:35.814 --> 01:06:38.317
[SCREAMING]

01:06:43.989 --> 01:06:45.324
Josh!

01:06:48.560 --> 01:06:51.330
- Josh!
- [MUFFLED SCREAMING]

01:06:52.397 --> 01:06:54.032
AARON:
Josh!

01:06:55.267 --> 01:06:57.402
[SCREAMING]

01:06:59.870 --> 01:07:02.340
- Josh!
- [SCREECHING INCREASES]

01:07:03.707 --> 01:07:05.843
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

01:07:09.580 --> 01:07:11.179
MISTY: Durant, when
we get out of here,

01:07:11.181 --> 01:07:13.149
I'm gonna make sure
you're held responsible

01:07:13.151 --> 01:07:14.984
- for what you've done.
- Well, that's what I want, too,

01:07:14.986 --> 01:07:16.419
but they'll hear about it
from me.

01:07:16.421 --> 01:07:17.786
Don't forget,
you signed an NDA!

01:07:17.788 --> 01:07:20.089
Oh, yeah, good luck finding it.
Or enforcing it.

01:07:20.091 --> 01:07:22.991
- Your legal counsel's dead.
- So, you wanna see us destroyed,

01:07:22.993 --> 01:07:26.196
all of mankind, so that
you can save what you value.

01:07:26.198 --> 01:07:29.198
See, we're not that different,
we just value different species.

01:07:29.200 --> 01:07:31.433
Oh, we're about as different
as two people can be.

01:07:31.435 --> 01:07:33.268
Okay, okay. If you guys
don't stop arguing

01:07:33.270 --> 01:07:35.740
I'm gonna feed myself
to these sharks. Okay?

01:07:38.975 --> 01:07:41.379
[♪♪♪]

01:07:43.381 --> 01:07:45.484
DANIEL [DISTANTLY]:
Leslie?

01:07:47.151 --> 01:07:48.650
Daniel?

01:07:48.652 --> 01:07:50.589
DANIEL:
Leslie?

01:07:56.460 --> 01:07:58.361
MISTY:
Daniel?

01:07:58.363 --> 01:08:00.498
- [GRUNTS]
- [WHEEL SQUEAKS]

01:08:01.366 --> 01:08:03.132
MISTY:
Daniel!

01:08:03.134 --> 01:08:05.935
Inside this pump?

01:08:05.937 --> 01:08:07.538
Yes.

01:08:19.951 --> 01:08:21.819
Daniel!

01:08:26.290 --> 01:08:28.126
[CREAKING]

01:08:38.603 --> 01:08:40.738
[CLANGING]

01:08:41.706 --> 01:08:43.707
What are you doing?

01:08:46.111 --> 01:08:48.680
What the hell are you doing?
Are you crazy?

01:08:49.679 --> 01:08:51.816
Have you lost your mind?

01:08:52.683 --> 01:08:54.685
Let's get out of here.

01:08:55.786 --> 01:08:57.685
You might have just
killed her!

01:08:57.688 --> 01:09:00.459
Those baby sharks
won't get to us now.

01:09:01.492 --> 01:09:03.660
I should kill you
right here.

01:09:03.662 --> 01:09:05.660
Yeah,
but you won't.

01:09:05.662 --> 01:09:07.694
Because you're not
a murderer.

01:09:07.697 --> 01:09:09.698
Besides,
if we make it topside,

01:09:09.701 --> 01:09:11.968
maybe you can get help
in time to save her.

01:09:11.970 --> 01:09:14.002
Think of it as
incentive.

01:09:14.005 --> 01:09:15.674
- Ugh!
- [THUDS]

01:09:17.006 --> 01:09:18.943
[♪♪♪]

01:09:24.046 --> 01:09:25.613
[♪♪♪]

01:09:25.616 --> 01:09:28.183
It's... Ahh!
It's jammed!

01:09:28.185 --> 01:09:30.020
Durant busted the door!

01:09:31.854 --> 01:09:34.089
Get topside!
Call for help!

01:09:34.091 --> 01:09:35.725
I'm going up.

01:09:35.727 --> 01:09:39.359
Try to look for another way out,
but I'm coming back!

01:09:39.362 --> 01:09:41.296
I'm coming back down!

01:09:41.299 --> 01:09:43.535
[PANTING]

01:09:46.604 --> 01:09:48.736
[METAL CREAKING]

01:09:48.738 --> 01:09:50.908
[♪♪♪]

01:09:52.343 --> 01:09:54.278
[GRUNTING]

01:10:16.300 --> 01:10:18.200
- [GRUNTS]
- [CLANGS]

01:10:18.202 --> 01:10:19.634
[PANTING]

01:10:19.636 --> 01:10:21.639
Where are you going?

01:10:26.545 --> 01:10:28.576
You forgot
where your loyalties lie.

01:10:28.578 --> 01:10:29.915
Man, go to hell!

01:10:30.980 --> 01:10:32.748
You know, I...
I get her.

01:10:32.750 --> 01:10:34.917
That woman's a fanatic.

01:10:34.919 --> 01:10:36.718
But you've been here,

01:10:36.720 --> 01:10:38.619
you've watched
what we've achieved

01:10:38.621 --> 01:10:39.922
in such a short time.

01:10:39.924 --> 01:10:42.191
You've contributed to it!

01:10:42.193 --> 01:10:44.826
I've got the answer
right here.

01:10:44.828 --> 01:10:48.397
We can access so much more

01:10:48.399 --> 01:10:50.432
of our brains' capabilities.

01:10:50.434 --> 01:10:52.168
I've done it,
I've felt it!

01:10:52.170 --> 01:10:55.137
I just need a little more
time to figure out

01:10:55.139 --> 01:10:58.073
- how to make it last....
- Anything for the project, huh?

01:10:58.075 --> 01:11:00.743
You know, I had commanders
like you in the military!

01:11:00.745 --> 01:11:03.111
Soldiers were just pieces
on a chessboard.

01:11:03.113 --> 01:11:05.146
It's one of the reasons
I got the hell out.

01:11:05.148 --> 01:11:07.816
Well, you need to get back in,
because the war is coming!

01:11:07.818 --> 01:11:10.619
- There is no war!
- Man against machine!

01:11:10.621 --> 01:11:12.788
You are so paranoid
that machines,

01:11:12.790 --> 01:11:14.789
robots, computers,
are gonna wipe us out!

01:11:14.791 --> 01:11:17.058
Let me tell you something,
from what I've seen,

01:11:17.060 --> 01:11:19.360
man is the real threat,
man is the real problem!

01:11:19.362 --> 01:11:22.530
You know, you have really
lost your way, Trent.

01:11:22.532 --> 01:11:24.366
I'm disappointed in you.

01:11:24.368 --> 01:11:27.671
Then, it's a good thing I don't
give a damn what you think.

01:11:31.341 --> 01:11:33.277
[CREAKING]

01:11:37.247 --> 01:11:39.183
[GASPS THEN PANTS]

01:11:45.389 --> 01:11:46.825
Daniel!

01:11:50.294 --> 01:11:51.927
Where are you?

01:11:51.929 --> 01:11:54.799
[♪♪♪]

01:11:58.836 --> 01:12:02.240
[GRUNTING, PANTING]

01:12:14.285 --> 01:12:15.819
Daniel?

01:12:17.755 --> 01:12:19.891
[♪♪♪]

01:12:30.702 --> 01:12:32.671
[WATER SPRAYING]

01:12:34.505 --> 01:12:37.339
Leslie! Leslie!

01:12:37.341 --> 01:12:38.941
No! No, no, no!

01:12:38.943 --> 01:12:40.709
C'mon!
Leslie...

01:12:40.711 --> 01:12:42.610
Leslie! No, no!
Don't go that way!

01:12:42.612 --> 01:12:46.748
No! No, don't! Come back!
Come back! Come back! No!

01:12:46.750 --> 01:12:48.984
[WHIMPERS]

01:12:48.986 --> 01:12:51.186
C'mon,
open this door!

01:12:51.188 --> 01:12:53.121
[SOBBING]

01:12:53.123 --> 01:12:55.926
Leslie! It's me!
Come here!

01:12:57.161 --> 01:12:58.860
Leslie, it's me!
Come here!

01:12:58.862 --> 01:13:00.829
- Daniel?
- Leslie!

01:13:00.831 --> 01:13:03.198
- Daniel!
- [SCREECHING]

01:13:03.200 --> 01:13:07.002
Get out of the water!
Get out of there!

01:13:07.004 --> 01:13:09.003
[SCREECHING INTENSIFIES]

01:13:09.005 --> 01:13:12.040
- Get out of the water!
- Daniel! Daniel!

01:13:12.042 --> 01:13:13.875
- Daniel! Oh, my God!
- Run!

01:13:13.877 --> 01:13:15.645
- Help me, Daniel!
- [SCREECHING]

01:13:15.647 --> 01:13:17.846
[SCREAMING]

01:13:17.848 --> 01:13:20.915
- Get off of her!
- Daniel, help me!

01:13:20.917 --> 01:13:22.484
[SHARKS SCREECHING]

01:13:22.486 --> 01:13:24.119
Daniel, help!
Daniel!

01:13:24.121 --> 01:13:25.553
Daniel!

01:13:25.555 --> 01:13:27.222
[GROANS]

01:13:27.224 --> 01:13:30.293
[BOTH SCREAMING]

01:13:30.295 --> 01:13:33.195
[SQUELCHING]

01:13:33.197 --> 01:13:34.733
Leslie!

01:13:35.599 --> 01:13:37.531
[♪♪♪]

01:13:37.533 --> 01:13:39.470
[SCREECHING CONTINUES]

01:13:47.344 --> 01:13:49.514
No!

01:13:55.452 --> 01:13:57.388
[PANTING]

01:14:03.595 --> 01:14:05.864
[MISTY PANTING]

01:14:14.004 --> 01:14:16.140
[♪♪♪]

01:14:20.377 --> 01:14:22.179
[GRUNTS]

01:14:23.547 --> 01:14:25.813
[GAS RUSHES]

01:14:25.815 --> 01:14:27.952
[PANTING]

01:14:29.953 --> 01:14:31.555
[GRUNTS]

01:14:41.398 --> 01:14:42.466
Shit.

01:14:49.872 --> 01:14:51.843
[♪♪♪]

01:15:10.595 --> 01:15:11.863
Shit.

01:15:21.004 --> 01:15:23.004
[PHONE BUTTONS BEEP]

01:15:23.006 --> 01:15:24.973
Mayday, Mayday,
Coast Guard.

01:15:24.975 --> 01:15:27.243
This is
Research Facility Akheilos.

01:15:27.245 --> 01:15:29.110
Requesting
immediate evacuation.

01:15:29.112 --> 01:15:31.446
We are taking on water,
we are without power,

01:15:31.448 --> 01:15:32.580
and we are on fire.

01:15:32.582 --> 01:15:34.783
We've suffered
major structural damage.

01:15:34.785 --> 01:15:36.218
Requesting
immediate evacuation.

01:15:36.220 --> 01:15:38.686
I say again,
requesting immediate evac.

01:15:38.688 --> 01:15:40.524
[PHONE LINE CRACKLES]

01:15:42.492 --> 01:15:44.428
[SHARKS SCREECHING]

01:15:53.970 --> 01:15:57.241
[♪♪♪]

01:16:01.545 --> 01:16:04.512
AARON: You are rocking this
whole staying alive thing.

01:16:04.514 --> 01:16:06.450
Now get to that pipe...

01:16:10.054 --> 01:16:11.786
Oh no, no, no, no...

01:16:11.788 --> 01:16:13.254
Oh, come on!

01:16:13.256 --> 01:16:15.591
No! This is so not fair!

01:16:15.593 --> 01:16:17.660
[YELLS]

01:16:17.662 --> 01:16:19.727
Goddamn it!

01:16:19.729 --> 01:16:21.899
Whoa! Whoa!

01:16:25.135 --> 01:16:27.438
[♪♪♪]

01:16:35.912 --> 01:16:37.678
Daniel?

01:16:37.680 --> 01:16:40.919
[MUTTERING]
Leslie...

01:16:43.821 --> 01:16:46.655
I'm sorry, man,
sincerely, I am,

01:16:46.657 --> 01:16:49.891
but right now, right now
we gotta keep moving, all right?

01:16:49.893 --> 01:16:51.328
Why?

01:16:53.063 --> 01:16:54.329
Just let me go.

01:16:54.331 --> 01:16:56.132
I'm not leaving you here.

01:16:56.134 --> 01:16:57.967
Just let me die.

01:16:57.969 --> 01:16:59.401
Snap out of it, Daniel!

01:16:59.403 --> 01:17:00.768
I can't do this on my own.

01:17:00.770 --> 01:17:03.472
Leslie wouldn't want you
to give up on her, huh?

01:17:03.474 --> 01:17:07.109
Why? She'd want you
to keep fighting.

01:17:07.111 --> 01:17:08.977
I know, I know
I barely knew her, man,

01:17:08.979 --> 01:17:11.879
but what I do know
is that she loved you.

01:17:11.881 --> 01:17:14.415
She'd want you to live.

01:17:14.417 --> 01:17:15.651
All right?

01:17:15.653 --> 01:17:17.485
So right now,
what you've got to do

01:17:17.487 --> 01:17:19.922
is you've got
to live for her.

01:17:19.924 --> 01:17:21.656
You got to live for her.

01:17:21.658 --> 01:17:23.991
- I have to live for her.
- You got to live for her.

01:17:23.993 --> 01:17:25.526
You can do this.

01:17:25.528 --> 01:17:26.561
[SNIFFS]

01:17:26.563 --> 01:17:28.530
I can do this.

01:17:28.532 --> 01:17:29.897
Yes, you can.

01:17:29.899 --> 01:17:31.734
Come on.

01:17:31.736 --> 01:17:33.071
Come on.

01:17:35.706 --> 01:17:38.009
[♪♪♪]

01:17:44.514 --> 01:17:45.548
[MISTY GRUNTING]

01:17:45.550 --> 01:17:46.682
Misty?

01:17:46.684 --> 01:17:49.750
- Oh, hey! Misty!
- Oh, my God! You're alive!

01:17:49.752 --> 01:17:51.154
- Oh!
- You're alive!

01:17:52.154 --> 01:17:53.558
Where are the others?

01:17:55.791 --> 01:17:57.661
They didn't make it.

01:18:01.197 --> 01:18:03.033
I'm so sorry.

01:18:04.868 --> 01:18:06.267
I have to live for her.

01:18:06.269 --> 01:18:07.869
Tell me you got
a way out of here.

01:18:07.871 --> 01:18:10.705
Yeah, there's an air shaft
on the other side of this door.

01:18:10.707 --> 01:18:12.540
Trent's should be topside
right now,

01:18:12.542 --> 01:18:14.609
- radioing for help.
- Thank God.

01:18:14.611 --> 01:18:17.145
Well, what are we waiting for?
Come on, let's go.

01:18:17.147 --> 01:18:18.579
Come on, help me
with this door.

01:18:18.581 --> 01:18:20.516
- AARON: All right.
- MISTY: Pull! Pull!

01:18:20.518 --> 01:18:22.017
[ALL GRUNTING]

01:18:22.019 --> 01:18:25.053
MISTY: Got it. All
right, stop, stop, stop.

01:18:25.055 --> 01:18:26.687
- What is it?
- [DISTANT SCREECHES]

01:18:26.689 --> 01:18:28.088
We're not alone.

01:18:28.090 --> 01:18:30.124
Go, go, go. Go!

01:18:30.126 --> 01:18:31.226
Wait, what about you...

01:18:31.228 --> 01:18:33.197
I'll be right behind you! Go!

01:18:34.965 --> 01:18:36.200
[PANTING]

01:18:38.100 --> 01:18:39.737
[MUTTERS INDISTINCTLY]

01:18:42.473 --> 01:18:43.774
Come on.

01:18:45.841 --> 01:18:48.278
[♪♪♪]

01:18:53.417 --> 01:18:54.883
Shit!

01:18:54.885 --> 01:18:56.754
Oh! Shit!

01:19:02.392 --> 01:19:05.162
Guys, get out of here! Go!

01:19:12.669 --> 01:19:14.002
Come on, Aaron.

01:19:14.004 --> 01:19:15.904
Almost there.

01:19:15.906 --> 01:19:17.338
One rung at a time.

01:19:17.340 --> 01:19:19.343
[MUFFLED THUD]

01:19:23.045 --> 01:19:24.514
Oh, shit.

01:19:29.053 --> 01:19:31.122
One rung at a time!

01:19:32.956 --> 01:19:34.890
Damn it. Ugh.

01:19:34.892 --> 01:19:37.260
Hurry, the waters are rising!

01:19:38.862 --> 01:19:40.161
TRENT:
All right!

01:19:40.163 --> 01:19:41.732
Give me the key.

